---
import LocationLayout from '../../../layouts/LocationLayout.astro';
import FAQSection from '../../../components/FAQSection.astro';
import locations from '../../../data/locations.json';
import pricing from '../../../data/pricing.json';
import services from '../../../data/services.json';

const loc = locations.locations[2];
const p = pricing.services.hullInspection;

const faqs = [
  { q: "Can you inspect mooring chains and tackle while inspecting my hull?", a: "While our primary service focuses on the hull itself, the Keelcrab's camera can visually inspect mooring chains, shackles, and ground tackle in the immediate vicinity of your vessel. If you'd like us to pay particular attention to your mooring hardware, let us know when booking and we'll factor in the extra time." },
  { q: "Is an underwater inspection useful for river-moored boats?", a: "Particularly so. River-moored vessels face unique challenges — silt accumulation around waterline fittings, faster anode depletion in brackish water, and debris impact damage from river flotsam. Regular inspections catch these issues early, before they become expensive repairs." },
  { q: "What's the visibility like underwater on the River Dart?", a: "Visibility on the Dart varies with tides, rainfall, and season — from reasonably clear to quite murky after heavy rain. The Keelcrab's built-in LED lighting system is designed for exactly these conditions, producing clear HD footage even in low-visibility harbour water. We'll schedule around spring tides and dry weather for the best results." },
];
---
<LocationLayout
  title="Hull Inspection in Dartmouth"
  description="Visual hull inspection on the River Dart. Monitor estuarine silt, invasive species, and antifoul degradation with HD video. From £10/metre. No lift-out required."
  locationName={loc.name} locationSlug={loc.slug} marina={loc.marina} tagline="Visual Hull Inspection on the River Dart"
  berths={loc.berths} maxVesselLength={loc.maxVesselLength} access={loc.access}
  foulingFactors={loc.foulingFactors} contentAngle={loc.contentAngle}
  heroImage="/images/locations/dartmouth-river.png"
  breadcrumbService="Hull Inspection" breadcrumbServiceSlug="hull-inspection"
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">
        <div class="content-main">
          <h2>Estuarine Conditions Make Dartmouth Inspections Uniquely Valuable</h2>
          <p>The River Dart throws curveballs at boat hulls that you simply don't encounter in open harbour marinas. Fluctuating salinity means your antifouling paint works in conditions it may not have been optimised for — most antifoul is formulated for consistent saltwater immersion, not the brackish tidal shifts of an estuary. Our HD inspection reveals exactly how your coating is holding up in these demanding conditions, often identifying degradation patterns months before they'd become obvious during an annual haul-out.</p>
          <p>For many Dartmouth owners, the biggest revelation from a first inspection is the volume of fine river silt that accumulates in hull recesses — around the keel root, inside rudder bearings, around through-hull fittings, and in any area where water flow is reduced. This silt isn't just cosmetic. It traps moisture against the hull surface, accelerates osmotic blistering in GRP hulls, and creates ideal conditions for anaerobic corrosion in steel and aluminium vessels. Catching it early with a £100 inspection is dramatically cheaper than dealing with the consequences later.</p>

          <h3>Invasive Species Monitoring on the Dart</h3>
          <p>Dart Harbour Authority has been increasingly vocal about the risk of invasive non-native species entering the estuary via hull fouling. Species like the carpet sea squirt (<em>Didemnum vexillum</em>) and Pacific oyster (<em>Magallana gigas</em>) have been identified in nearby waters, and hull fouling is a primary vector for their spread. Our inspections can identify unusual growth patterns and document them with HD video — providing evidence that supports both your biosecurity obligations and the harbour authority's monitoring efforts.</p>
          <p>If you're planning to move your boat from the Dart to another harbour (or vice versa), an inspection before departure is good practice. It demonstrates due diligence on biosecurity and gives you peace of mind that you're not inadvertently transporting organisms between water bodies.</p>

          <h3>Swing Mooring Inspections</h3>
          <p>Boats on Dart Harbour swing moorings are among the hardest to inspect without specialist equipment. You can't easily crane-lift a vessel from a river mooring, and hiring a commercial diver for a mooring inspection is disproportionately expensive for most private boat owners. Our portable Keelcrab Pro system changes this — we can reach mooring-based vessels by tender and deploy the robot from alongside, providing the same quality of inspection you'd get at a marina berth.</p>
          <p>Given the accelerated fouling rates on river moorings, we recommend Dartmouth mooring owners inspect at least twice per year — once pre-season (March/April) and once mid-season (July/August). This catches any deterioration before it becomes a costly problem.</p>

          <div class="disclaimer-box">
            <p><strong>⚠️ Important:</strong> Our inspection is a visual condition report delivered by robotic technology. It is not a qualified marine survey and does not replace the opinion of a certified marine surveyor. We do not provide structural assessments, osmosis testing, or MCA compliance surveys.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="price-box">
            <span class="price-box__label">Hull Inspection</span>
            <span class="price-box__amount">£{p.pricePerMetre}</span>
            <span class="price-box__unit">per metre</span>
            <span class="price-box__min">Min: £{p.minimumCharge}</span>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn--primary" style="width:100%;margin-top:var(--space-md)">Book an Inspection</a>
          </div>
          <div class="sidebar-info">
            <h4>What We Look For on the Dart</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Silt deposits in keel root and hull recesses</li>
              <li>Antifouling degradation from brackish water</li>
              <li>Invasive species indicators</li>
              <li>Through-hull fitting condition</li>
              <li>Mooring chain wear and attachment points</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="other-services">
            <h4>Also in Dartmouth</h4>
            <a href="/locations/dartmouth/hull-cleaning">Hull Cleaning →</a>
            <a href="/locations/dartmouth/maintenance-plans">Maintenance Plans →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section__header">
        <h2>Why Inspect Your Hull?</h2>
        <p class="section__subtitle">The real, practical reasons to know what's happening below your waterline — before problems become expensive.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid--3">
        {services.services[1].benefits.map((benefit) => (
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="card__title">{benefit.title}</h3>
            <p class="card__text">{benefit.description}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <!-- FAQs -->
  <FAQSection faqs={faqs} />

</LocationLayout>

<style>
  .content-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr; gap: var(--space-3xl); align-items: start; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) { .content-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .content-main p { color: var(--text-light); margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: 1.8; }
  .content-main h3 { margin-top: var(--space-2xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-md); font-size: 1.25rem; }
  .disclaimer-box { background: rgba(231,76,60,0.08); border: 1px solid rgba(231,76,60,0.2); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: var(--space-lg); margin-top: var(--space-xl); }
  .disclaimer-box p { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-light); margin: 0; }
  .price-box { background: var(--surface); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-xl); text-align: center; margin-bottom: var(--space-xl); position: sticky; top: calc(var(--header-height) + var(--space-lg)); }
  .price-box__label { display: block; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: var(--space-sm); }
  .price-box__amount { display: block; font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: 3rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--primary); }
  .price-box__unit { display: block; color: var(--text-light); font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .price-box__min { display: block; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.8rem; margin-top: var(--space-xs); }
  .sidebar-info { background: var(--surface); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-xl); }
  .sidebar-info h4 { font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: var(--space-md); }
  .sidebar-info ul { list-style: none; }
  .sidebar-info li { padding: var(--space-xs) 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-light); }
  .sidebar-info li::before { content: '→ '; color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; }
  .other-services { background: var(--surface); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-xl); }
  .other-services h4 { font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: var(--space-md); }
  .other-services a { display: block; padding: var(--space-sm) 0; color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; }
</style>
